{
  "texts": [
    "Ms are no speakers.",
    "My analysis so far is congenial to the recent study by Green and Michel (2022).",
    "In particular, they agree that there is no speaking that is not acting.",
    "They analyze in detail the case of what they call proxy speech acts, e.g.",
    "when a representative of a city council performs a speech act that she can only succeed at by assuming the role of a representative of that council, not by herself."
  ]
}